# Maestro Social Hub — Brainstorm & Implementation Plan

> **Maestro** is an AI-centric online university. This document outlines the vision, feature brainstorm, and phased build plan for its social platform — a place where students connect, collaborate, share work, and grow together.

---

## 1 · Vision & Core Pillars

| Pillar | Description |
|---|---|
| **Learn Together** | Students on the same course find each other, form study groups, and work through lessons in real time |
| **Build in Public** | Every student has a portfolio that grows as they complete projects — a living résumé |
| **AI-Native** | AI is woven into the platform: smart feeds, study recommendations, writing assistance, code review |
| **Community First** | Social features (feed, reactions, comments, DMs) make the platform feel alive and sticky |

---

## 2 · Feature Brainstorm

### 2.1 Authentication & Accounts
- Email + password registration with email verification
- OAuth (Google, GitHub) for quick sign-up
- Role system: **Student**, **Instructor**, **Admin**
- Onboarding wizard: pick courses, set interests, upload avatar

### 2.2 Social Feed (The "Quad")
- Chronological + algorithmic feed of posts from people you follow and your course cohorts
- Post types:
  - **Text** — status updates, questions, thoughts
  - **Rich Media** — images, embedded videos, code snippets with syntax highlighting
  - **Project Showcase** — link a portfolio piece directly into the feed with a preview card
  - **Poll** — quick polls for study group decisions or community engagement
  - **Milestone** — auto-generated posts when a student completes a course, earns a badge, or ships a project
- Reactions (🔥 Brilliant, 💡 Insightful, 🤝 Helpful, 👏 Congrats) — more expressive than a plain "like"
- Threaded comments with inline code, markdown support, and @mentions
- Bookmarking / saving posts
- Share / repost to your own feed
- Content moderation queue for admins

### 2.3 User Profiles
- **Profile Header** — avatar, banner image, display name, headline (e.g. "AI Engineering Student · Cohort 7"), location, links (GitHub, LinkedIn, personal site)
- **Bio Section** — rich text about-me
- **Stats Bar** — courses completed, projects shipped, streak days, reputation score
- **Activity Tab** — recent posts, comments, and reactions
- **Portfolio Tab** — (see 2.4)
- **Courses Tab** — enrolled courses with progress bars
- **Connections Tab** — followers / following list
- **Badges & Achievements** — earned through platform activity (first project, 30-day streak, top contributor, etc.)

### 2.4 Portfolio
- Grid or list view of completed projects
- Each project card contains:
  - Title, description, thumbnail/cover image
  - Tech stack tags
  - Link to live demo / GitHub repo
  - Related course
  - Peer endorsements ("I worked with them on this")
- Drag-and-drop reordering to curate featured order
- **Public shareable link** — students can share their Maestro portfolio externally (like a mini personal website)
- PDF export for resumes / applications

### 2.5 Course Groups ("Cohorts")
- Auto-created group for every course offering
- Group features:
  - **Discussion board** — threaded Q&A organized by lesson/module
  - **Member directory** — see who's in your cohort with progress status
  - **Study rooms** — small breakout groups (2–5 people) for collaborative learning
  - **Resource sharing** — pin helpful links, notes, files
  - **Group progress tracker** — visual chart of cohort's collective progress
- **Study Buddy Matching** — AI matches students based on pace, timezone, learning style, and availability
- **Office Hours** — scheduled sessions where instructors or TAs are available (integrated with calendar)

### 2.6 Messaging & Notifications
- **Direct Messages** — 1:1 real-time chat with markdown + code snippet support
- **Group Chat** — for study rooms and cohort sub-groups
- **Notification Center** — bell icon with categorized notifications:
  - Social (likes, comments, follows, mentions)
  - Academic (new lesson available, assignment due, grade posted)
  - Collaboration (study room invite, buddy match, group activity)
- Email digest (daily/weekly summary, configurable)
- Push notifications (opt-in)

### 2.7 AI-Powered Features
- **Smart Feed Ranking** — surface posts relevant to your courses and interests
- **AI Study Assistant** — chatbot that can answer questions about lesson material, link to relevant posts, and suggest study partners
- **Code Review Bot** — students can submit code snippets for AI-powered review before posting to their portfolio
- **Writing Assistant** — help students write better posts, project descriptions, and bios
- **Content Summarization** — TL;DR summaries for long discussion threads
- **Suggested Connections** — "Students like you also follow…"

### 2.8 Discovery & Search
- **Global Search** — search posts, people, projects, courses, and groups
- **Explore Page** — trending posts, featured portfolios, popular courses
- **Hashtags / Topics** — tag content with topics like `#MachineLearning`, `#WebDev`, `#Cohort7`
- **Student Spotlight** — weekly featured student profile chosen by AI + admin

### 2.9 Gamification & Engagement
- **XP System** — earn XP for completing lessons, posting, commenting, helping peers
- **Levels & Ranks** — Novice → Scholar → Expert → Maestro (title!)
- **Streak Tracking** — daily login / study streaks with visual flame counter
- **Leaderboards** — per course, per cohort, and global (opt-in)
- **Achievement Badges** — milestone-based (first post, first project, 100 comments, etc.)

### 2.10 Admin & Moderation
- Admin dashboard: user management, content moderation, analytics
- Report system for posts/comments/messages
- Auto-moderation with AI content filtering
- Instructor tools: pin announcements, create assignments, manage cohort settings

