## 3 · Information Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Landing / Auth] --> B[Home Feed - The Quad]
    B --> C[Post Detail]
    B --> D[Create Post]
    B --> E[Profile]
    E --> E1[Activity]
    E --> E2[Portfolio]
    E --> E3[Courses]
    E --> E4[Connections]
    B --> F[Explore / Discover]
    B --> G[Course Groups]
    G --> G1[Discussion Board]
    G --> G2[Study Rooms]
    G --> G3[Member Directory]
    B --> H[Messages]
    H --> H1[DM Thread]
    H --> H2[Group Chat]
    B --> I[Notifications]
    B --> J[Settings]
    B --> K[Admin Dashboard]
```

---

## 4 · Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| **Framework** | Next.js 16 (App Router) | Already scaffolded, SSR + API routes in one project |
| **Styling** | Tailwind CSS 4 | Already installed, rapid UI development |
| **Language** | TypeScript | Type safety across the full stack |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL via Supabase | Auth, real-time subscriptions, row-level security, storage — all-in-one |
| **Auth** | Supabase Auth | Email/password, OAuth providers, JWT sessions |
| **Real-time** | Supabase Realtime | Live feed updates, chat, notifications |
| **File Storage** | Supabase Storage | Avatars, banners, project images |
| **AI** | OpenAI API / Vercel AI SDK | Chat assistant, code review, smart feed |
| **State Management** | React Context + SWR/React Query | Client-side caching and real-time sync |
| **Deployment** | Vercel | Seamless Next.js deployment, edge functions |

---

## 5 · Database Schema (High-Level)

```mermaid
erDiagram
    USERS ||--o{ POSTS : creates
    USERS ||--o{ COMMENTS : writes
    USERS ||--o{ PORTFOLIO_PROJECTS : owns
    USERS ||--o{ FOLLOWS : follows
    USERS ||--o{ ENROLLMENTS : enrolls_in
    USERS ||--o{ MESSAGES : sends
    USERS ||--o{ NOTIFICATIONS : receives
    USERS ||--o{ BADGES : earns

    POSTS ||--o{ COMMENTS : has
    POSTS ||--o{ REACTIONS : receives
    POSTS ||--o{ BOOKMARKS : saved_by

    COURSES ||--o{ ENROLLMENTS : has
    COURSES ||--o{ COURSE_GROUPS : creates
    COURSE_GROUPS ||--o{ STUDY_ROOMS : contains
    COURSE_GROUPS ||--o{ DISCUSSIONS : has

    STUDY_ROOMS ||--o{ STUDY_ROOM_MEMBERS : includes
```

### Key Tables
- **users** — id, email, username, display_name, avatar_url, banner_url, bio, headline, links, role, xp, level, streak, created_at
- **posts** — id, author_id, content, type (text/media/showcase/poll/milestone), media_urls, course_group_id (optional), created_at
- **comments** — id, post_id, author_id, parent_comment_id (for threading), content, created_at
- **reactions** — id, post_id, user_id, type (brilliant/insightful/helpful/congrats)
- **follows** — follower_id, following_id, created_at
- **portfolio_projects** — id, user_id, title, description, thumbnail_url, demo_url, repo_url, tech_stack[], course_id, sort_order, created_at
- **courses** — id, title, description, thumbnail_url, instructor_id
- **enrollments** — id, user_id, course_id, progress_pct, enrolled_at
- **course_groups** — id, course_id, name, description
- **study_rooms** — id, group_id, name, max_members, created_by
- **messages** — id, sender_id, receiver_id, room_id, content, read_at, created_at
- **notifications** — id, user_id, type, reference_id, message, read, created_at
- **badges** — id, name, description, icon_url, criteria
- **user_badges** — user_id, badge_id, earned_at
- **bookmarks** — user_id, post_id, created_at

---

## 6 · Phased Implementation Plan

### Phase 1 — Foundation (Week 1–2)
| Task | Details |
|---|---|
| Set up Supabase | Create project, configure auth providers, set up database tables |
| Auth system | Sign up, sign in, sign out, OAuth (Google/GitHub), protected routes |
| Core layout | App shell: sidebar nav, top bar, responsive mobile layout |
| Design system | Color palette, typography (Inter/Outfit), component primitives (Button, Input, Card, Avatar, Badge) |
| User settings | Basic settings page: edit name, email, password, avatar |

### Phase 2 — Social Feed (Week 3–4)
| Task | Details |
|---|---|
| Post creation | Rich text editor with markdown, image upload, code blocks |
| Feed page | Infinite scroll feed with post cards |
| Post types | Text, media, showcase, poll, milestone |
| Reactions | Reaction picker with counts |
| Comments | Threaded comments with markdown |
| Bookmarks | Save/unsave posts, bookmarks page |

### Phase 3 — Profiles & Portfolios (Week 5–6)
| Task | Details |
|---|---|
| Profile page | Header, bio, stats bar, tabbed layout |
| Activity tab | User's posts and comments |
| Portfolio tab | Project grid with CRUD, drag-and-drop reorder |
| Courses tab | Enrolled courses with progress |
| Connections | Follow/unfollow, followers/following lists |
| Public profile | Shareable external link |

### Phase 4 — Course Groups & Collaboration (Week 7–8)
| Task | Details |
|---|---|
| Course catalog | Browse/search courses |
| Course groups | Auto-created cohort groups |
| Discussion boards | Threaded Q&A per module |
| Study rooms | Create/join rooms, member management |
| Study Buddy Match | AI matching algorithm |
| Member directory | Search cohort members, filter by progress |

### Phase 5 — Messaging & Notifications (Week 9–10)
| Task | Details |
|---|---|
| DMs | Real-time 1:1 messaging |
| Group chat | Study room integrated chat |
| Notification center | Bell icon, categorized notifications |
| Email digests | Configurable daily/weekly summaries |

### Phase 6 — AI Features & Gamification (Week 11–12)
| Task | Details |
|---|---|
| AI Study Assistant | In-app chatbot for course Q&A |
| Code Review Bot | Submit code for AI review |
| Smart Feed | AI-ranked content |
| XP & Levels | XP tracking, level progression |
| Badges | Achievement system with criteria |
| Leaderboards | Per-course and global rankings |
| Streaks | Daily activity tracking |

### Phase 7 — Polish & Launch (Week 13–14)
| Task | Details |
|---|---|
| Admin dashboard | User management, moderation, analytics |
| Search & Explore | Global search, trending content, hashtags |
| Performance | Optimize queries, caching, lazy loading |
| Accessibility | WCAG compliance, keyboard nav, screen reader support |
| Mobile polish | Responsive refinements, touch interactions |
| SEO | Meta tags, OG images, sitemap |
| Testing | E2E tests, integration tests, load testing |

---

## 7 · UI/UX Direction

### Look & Feel
- **Dark-mode first** with light mode toggle — matches the "tech-forward AI university" brand
- **Glassmorphism accents** — frosted glass cards, subtle blur effects
- Deep indigo/violet primary palette with electric cyan accents
- Smooth micro-animations: card hover lifts, reaction pop-ins, skeleton loading states
- **Typography**: Inter for body, Outfit for headings — clean and modern

### Key Screens (Priority Order)
1. **Auth** — Cinematic landing with animated gradient, clean login/register forms
2. **The Quad (Feed)** — Left sidebar (nav), center feed, right sidebar (trending / suggested connections)
3. **Post Composer** — Modal or slide-up panel with rich editor
4. **Profile** — Hero banner + avatar overlap, tabbed content
5. **Portfolio** — Masonry grid of project cards with hover previews
6. **Course Group** — Discussion board with collapsible threads, member sidebar
7. **Messages** — Slack-like layout with conversation list + chat pane
8. **Notifications** — Dropdown + full page with filters

---

## 8 · Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- **Unit tests** (Vitest): utility functions, data transformations, form validation
- **Component tests** (React Testing Library): post card rendering, comment threading, reaction toggling
- **E2E tests** (Playwright): full auth flow, post CRUD, profile editing, navigation
  - Command: `npx playwright test`

### Browser Verification
- Use the browser tool to visually verify key screens after each phase
- Check responsive layouts at mobile (375px), tablet (768px), and desktop (1280px) breakpoints

### Manual Verification
- After each phase, the user should:
  1. Run `npm run dev` and navigate through the new features
  2. Test auth flows (sign up, sign in, sign out)
  3. Create posts, add comments, react to content
  4. Edit profile and add portfolio projects
  5. Join course groups and create study rooms
  6. Send messages and check notifications

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Provider**: This plan proposes **Supabase** (PostgreSQL + Auth + Realtime + Storage) as an all-in-one backend. If you prefer a different stack (e.g., Prisma + separate auth like NextAuth, or Firebase), let me know and I'll adjust.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **AI Provider**: The plan uses the **OpenAI API** (via Vercel AI SDK) for AI features. If you have a preferred AI provider or want to use a self-hosted model, let me know.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Scope for v1**: This is an ambitious feature set. Would you like to start with a focused MVP (Phases 1–3: Auth + Feed + Profiles/Portfolios) and iterate, or do you want to plan for the full scope from the start?

> [!NOTE]
> **Tailwind CSS 4** is already configured in the project. The plan builds on the existing Next.js 16 + Tailwind 4 scaffold.
